glish theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705197,"age":100,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Margery Nowers was born in 1355, in Knossington, Leicestershire, England, her father, Ralph Nowers, was 55 and her mother, Margaret Buckland, was 51. She married William Wilcockes I in 1381, in Knossington, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died in Rotherham, Yorkshire, England."},"et":{"1355–":"1355–Surnud","1355–Female":"1355–Surnud","1362–Female":"1362–Surnud","1331–1390":"1331–1390","1382–Male":"1382–Surnud","1385–1430":"1385–1430","1300–Male":"1300–Surnud","1304–Female":"1304–Surnud","1385":"1385","1362":"1362","1382":"1382","1381":"1381","1390":"1390","1304":"1304","1335":"1335","1455":"1455","1355":"1355","1300":"1300","1430":"1430","1331":"1331","about 1385":"umbes 1385","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","England":"England","Knossington, Leicestershire, England":"Knossington, Leicestershire, England","Rotherham, Yorkshire, England":"Rotherham, Yorkshire, England","Knossington, Leicester, England, Great Britain":"Knossington, Leicestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1355–":"1355–Kuollut","1355–Female":"1355–Kuollut"